[{},{"attrs":{"title":"API: The server Property","description":"Nuxt.js let you define the server connection variables for your application inside `nuxt.config.js`."},"body":"<h1><a id=\"the-server-property\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#the-server-property\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>The server Property</h1><ul>\n<li>Type: <code>Object</code></li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Nuxt.js let you define the server connection variables for your application inside <code>nuxt.config.js</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><a id=\"basic-example-code-nuxt-config-js-code-\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#basic-example-code-nuxt-config-js-code-\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Basic example (<code>nuxt.config.js</code>):</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">default</span> {\n  <span class=\"hljs-attr\">server</span>: {\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">port</span>: <span class=\"hljs-number\">8000</span>, <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// default: 3000</span>\n    host: <span class=\"hljs-string\">'0.0.0.0'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// default: localhost,</span>\n    timing: <span class=\"hljs-literal\">false</span>\n  }\n}</code></pre><p>This lets you specify the <a href=\"/faq/host-port\">host and port</a> for your Nuxt.js server instance.</p>\n<h2><a id=\"example-using-https-configuration\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#example-using-https-configuration\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Example using HTTPS configuration</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">import</span> path <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\">'path'</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">import</span> fs <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\">'fs'</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">default</span> {\n  <span class=\"hljs-attr\">server</span>: {\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">https</span>: {\n      <span class=\"hljs-attr\">key</span>: fs.readFileSync(path.resolve(__dirname, <span class=\"hljs-string\">'server.key'</span>)),\n      <span class=\"hljs-attr\">cert</span>: fs.readFileSync(path.resolve(__dirname, <span class=\"hljs-string\">'server.crt'</span>))\n    }\n  }\n}</code></pre><h2><a id=\"example-using-sockets-configuration\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#example-using-sockets-configuration\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Example using sockets configuration</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">default</span> {\n  <span class=\"hljs-attr\">server</span>: {\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">socket</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\">'/tmp/nuxt.socket'</span>\n  }\n}</code></pre><h2><a id=\"timing\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#timing\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>timing</h2><ul>\n<li>Type: <code>Object</code> or <code>Boolean</code></li>\n<li>Default: <code>false</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Enabling the <code>server.timing</code> option adds a middleware to measure the time elapsed during server-side rendering and adds it to the headers as &#39;Server-Timing&#39;</p>\n<h3><a id=\"example-using-timing-configuration\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#example-using-timing-configuration\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Example using timing configuration</h3><p><code>server.timing</code> can be an object for providing options. Currently, only <code>total</code> is supported (which directly tracks the whole time spent on server-side rendering)</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">default</span> {\n  <span class=\"hljs-attr\">server</span>: {\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">timing</span>: {\n      <span class=\"hljs-attr\">total</span>: <span class=\"hljs-literal\">true</span>\n    }\n  }\n}</code></pre><h3><a id=\"using-timing-api\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#using-timing-api\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Using timing api</h3><p>The <code>timing</code> api is also injected into the <code>response</code> on server-side when <code>server.time</code> is enabled.</p>\n<h4><a id=\"syntax\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#syntax\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Syntax</h4><pre><code class=\"hljs js\">res.timing.start(name, description)\nres.timing.end(name)</code></pre><h4><a id=\"example-using-timing-in-servermiddleware\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#example-using-timing-in-servermiddleware\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>Example using timing in servermiddleware</h4><pre><code class=\"hljs js\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">function</span> (<span class=\"hljs-params\">req, res, next</span>) </span>{\n  res.timing.start(<span class=\"hljs-string\">'midd'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\">'Middleware timing description'</span>)\n  <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// server side operation..</span>\n  <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// ...</span>\n  res.timing.end(<span class=\"hljs-string\">'midd'</span>)\n  next()\n}</code></pre><p>Then <code>server-timing</code> head will be included in response header like:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">Server-Timing: midd;desc=<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Middleware timing description\"</span>;dur=2.4</code></pre><p>Please refer to <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Server-Timing\">Server-Timing MDN</a> for more details.</p>\n","docLink":"https://github.com/nuxt/docs/blob/master/en/api/configuration-server.md"}]